    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1208<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJJ2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCloy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">
                            <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Department</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-26">26 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 341. To <gloss target="#t_AG1">AG</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> for <persName corresp="#p_SMD1"
                        >Sommers</persName> Office Assistant Secretary of <gloss target="#t_War1"
                        >War</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CAD1">CAD</gloss> signed <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJJ2">McCloy</persName>.</p>
                <p>Reference <gloss target="#t_War1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">War</hi>
                    </gloss> 38253<note n="1" xml:id="d1208fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1206">Document No. 1206</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> and I approve the addition of a
                    paragraph reading as follows along the lines suggested by British.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“You should as far as possible administer the area, on following
                        lines:—Yugoslav system of national committees should in general be
                        discontinued in whole area, and Italian system reinstalled. In predominantly
                        Yugoslav towns and villages, token Yugoslav administration might be retained
                        and national committee used in advisory capacity.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p rend="flushleft">This is substantially <persName corresp="#p_LRA1"
                        >Lovett</persName>’s suggestion as reported by you.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
